OL,3,CIndia swelters in record-breaking 50C
OL,4,Cheatwave
OL,6,FApril, May and June are hot in most
OL,7,Fparts of India before monsoon rains
OL,8,Fbring cooler temperatures, but warm
OL,9,Fweather has been getting more intense
OL,10,Facross the past decade.
OL,12,FOne study found that heatwaves have
OL,13,Fkilled more than 24,000 people in the
OL,14,Fcountry since 1992.
OL,16,FThe increase in heat events in coming
OL,17,Fyears could threaten India's
OL,18,Fdevelopment, and risk reversing its
OL,19,Fprogress on poverty alleviation,
OL,20,Fhealth and economic growth,
OL,21,Fresearchers said.
